.SH NAME
Location.hostname \- Location: hostname property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]hostname\f[B]\f[R] property of the \f[CR]Location\f[R]
interface is a string containing either the domain name or IP address of
the location URL.
If the URL does not have a hostname, this property contains an empty
string, \f[CR]\[dq]\[dq]\f[R].
IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are normalized, such as stripping leading zeros,
and domain names are converted to \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internationalized_domain_name
IDN
.UE \c
\&.
.PP
See \f[CR]URL.hostname\f[R] for more information.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
console.log(window.location.hostname);
\f[I]// developer.mozilla.org\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] anchor = document.createElement(\[dq]a\[dq]);
anchor.href = \[dq]https://developer.mozilla.org:4097/\[dq];
console.log(anchor.hostname === \[dq]developer.mozilla.org\[dq]);
\f[I]// The port number is not included in hostname\f[R]
.EE
